In the lower kingdom, Nature does indeed make an acid of the
volatile, and an Alcali of the acid, and even if something appears quite
volatile, it yet contains its acid part and Alcali, although the volatile is
preponderant, which prevents the acid and Alcali from dominating.
But if the Acidum prevails, it associates again with its like and readily
absorbs the other Acidum.
